The SVN repo is the most current version of your package as far as Bioconductor goes. Unfortunately, you have totally unrelated histories by the looks of it. (This should show up as an error, when you try to ?merge?, i.e `git merge upstream/master`)

I would suggest moving forward with the new git repo, after the transition is done on August 16th. I would not ?delete? the repository you have per say, and keep a backup. 

